{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":37975,"name":"Haukinger","username":"Haukinger","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/haukinger/{size}/3670_2.png","created_at":"2020-06-22T20:04:36.102Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi there,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm on windows and my fragment shader does some raymarching. It writes to the frame buffer just fine, but I have no idea how I can write to another render target and how to read that from the application. I would like to get a buffer that for each pixel contains the world coordinates of the end point of the ray that produced the color of the pixel. I hoped that something along the line of fragData[1] = vec4(rayX, rayY, rayZ, 0.0) would do the job, but I either get index out of bounds or and empty bitmap or no rendered image at all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCan you point me to documentation or an example?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-06-22T20:04:36.102Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":6.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6218,"topic_slug":"write-to-two-render-targets","display_username":"Haukinger","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1351,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37980,"name":"ab4daa","username":"ab4daa","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/d26b3c/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-06-23T03:15:54.086Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think you could take a look at Deferred render path which output 4 targets(viewport, albedo, normal and depth) and use them in following render command.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"onebox githubblob\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Deferred.xml#L9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Deferred.xml#L9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eurho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Deferred.xml#L9\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"onebox\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-xml\"\u003e\u003col class=\"start lines\" start=\"1\" style=\"counter-reset: li-counter 0 ;\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"albedo\" sizedivisor=\"1 1\" format=\"rgba\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"normal\" sizedivisor=\"1 1\" format=\"rgba\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"depth\" sizedivisor=\"1 1\" format=\"lineardepth\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"1 1 1 1\" output=\"depth\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"deferred\" marktostencil=\"true\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"gbuffer\"\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;output index=\"0\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli class=\"selected\"\u003e        \u0026lt;output index=\"1\" name=\"albedo\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;output index=\"2\" name=\"normal\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;output index=\"3\" name=\"depth\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"lightvolumes\" vs=\"DeferredLight\" ps=\"DeferredLight\"\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"albedo\" name=\"albedo\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"normal\" name=\"normal\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"depth\" name=\"depth\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eand its shader part(define DEFERRED)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"onebox githubblob\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/HLSL/LitSolid.hlsl#L285\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/HLSL/LitSolid.hlsl#L285\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eurho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/HLSL/LitSolid.hlsl#L285\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"onebox\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-hlsl\"\u003e\u003col class=\"start lines\" start=\"275\" style=\"counter-reset: li-counter 274 ;\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #ifdef LIGHTMAP\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        finalColor += Sample2D(EmissiveMap, iTexCoord2).rgb * diffColor.rgb;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #endif\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #ifdef EMISSIVEMAP\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        finalColor += cMatEmissiveColor * Sample2D(EmissiveMap, iTexCoord.xy).rgb;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #else\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        finalColor += cMatEmissiveColor;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #endif\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    oColor = float4(GetFog(finalColor, fogFactor), 1.0);\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli class=\"selected\"\u003e    oAlbedo = fogFactor * float4(diffColor.rgb, specIntensity);\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    oNormal = float4(normal * 0.5 + 0.5, specPower);\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    oDepth = iWorldPos.w;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e#else\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    // Ambient \u0026amp; per-vertex lighting\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    float3 finalColor = iVertexLight * diffColor.rgb;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #ifdef AO\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        // If using AO, the vertex light ambient is black, calculate occluded ambient here\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        finalColor += Sample2D(EmissiveMap, iTexCoord2).rgb * cAmbientColor.rgb * diffColor.rgb;\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    #endif\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-06-23T03:15:54.086Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":5.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6218,"topic_slug":"write-to-two-render-targets","display_username":"ab4daa","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Deferred.xml#L9","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Deferred.xml at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":0},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/HLSL/LitSolid.hlsl#L285","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/LitSolid.hlsl at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":867,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37984,"name":"Haukinger","username":"Haukinger","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/haukinger/{size}/3670_2.png","created_at":"2020-06-23T15:55:42.926Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks a lot, I made progress. My render path is this now\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"albedo\" rtsizedivisor=\"1 1\" format=\"rgba\" /\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"0 0 0 0\" output=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"0 0 0 0\" output=\"albedo\" /\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"deferred\" metadata=\"gbuffer\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;output index=\"0\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;output index=\"1\" name=\"albedo\" /\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/renderpath\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand the technique is\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;technique vs=\"MyShader\" ps=\"MyShader\" vsdefines=\"NOUV\" psdefines=\"DEFERRED\" \u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"deferred\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/technique\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand the shader writes to fragData[1] without visible errors, but also without visible results.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôve created a texture and assigned it to rendertarget 1, but whenever I do GetData on that texture, it‚Äôs all zero. If I make the shader write the additional data to gl_FragColor (that is, fragData[0], isn‚Äôt it?), the data looks good.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôve set the texture‚Äôs usage to rendertarget, anything else I might be missing?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: I‚Äôve added the texture to the resource cache, and suddenly it contains data \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-06-23T16:56:26.798Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":19.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6218,"topic_slug":"write-to-two-render-targets","display_username":"Haukinger","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1351,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[37975,37980,37984]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,883]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7081,"title":"Install Urho3D Library - Windows 10 - rake build - \"project does not exist\"","fancy_title":"Install Urho3D Library - Windows 10 - rake build - \u0026ldquo;project does not exist\u0026rdquo;","s